Meet <b>Juan</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Juan lives at <a href='/home/?user=man5632'>4248 Hill Street</a> in Metro Park, and has been a citizen since September 16th, 2004. The location of his house allows him to be as close to downtown Millsberry as possible, which is where most of the action can be found. He's so close, in fact, that it just takes him a few minutes to reach the entertainment complex. What a great place to live!<br><br>As anyone can see, Juan is very athletic! His favorite sport is basketball, which he enjoys practicing at school. You should see how good he is at shooting hoops! He's so good that, sometimes, the entire gym class will stop what they're doing, just so they can watch and cheer him on while he's practicing. Basketball season is starting soon, and everybody is sure that Juan is going to be the star of the team!<br><br>Juan also likes animals, and is known for being very kind to strays. It's one of the many charming aspects of his personality. This, combined with his skill at basketball and his ability to work well with computers, makes Juan a very popular guy at Millsberry Academy.<br><br>If you'd like to meet Juan, just drop by his house. It's painted his favorite color, which is bright red. His other favorite colors include silver and gold.<br><br>After school, Juan enjoys hanging out at the mall with his friends. He's on the lookout for a new CD, preferably an album of rap, pop, or reggae songs. After Juan is done hanging out at the mall, he enjoys going to the Millsberry Arcade and playing the great new games there. Juan also enjoys collecting cards, so don't be too surprised if you run into him at a card shop.</div>
